  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Waldorf Salad #2</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Salad</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Mayonnaise</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Apples</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Yogurt; plain</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Celery stalks</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Sugar; granulated</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Walnuts; chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Lemon juice</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Date: Thu, 23 May 1996 22:05:10 -0500
  
  From: LD Goss &lt;ldgoss@METRONET.COM&gt;
  
  Recipe By: Foodview
  
  In small salad bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt and lemon juice, to taste.
  Core apples, cut into bite size pieces, dice celery. Add both to salad
  bowl, fold in nuts. Chill up to two hours. Toss before serving. variations:
  bananas &amp; pecans or in the summer peaches and peanuts from.
  
